FBIS4-35451 "drnes105_l_94020" FBIS-NES-94-105 Daily Report 1 Jun 1994 ISRAEL Motion on Transfer of Water Sources Rejected Motion on Transfer of Water Sources Rejected TA0106135494 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1200 GMT 1 Jun 94 TA0106135494 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el Hebrew BFN [Text] The Knesset plenum rejected a proposed bill by Likud Knesset Member [MK] Eliyahu Ben-Elisar that any political agreement that transfers responsibility for water resources from Israel would require the approval of at least 80 MK's. MK Ben-Elisar said that if the water resources are under Palestinian control there is a danger that they will try to dry us up. Our correspondent Hayim Hecht reports that the motion was rejected by a majority of one.
